          <h2>Physical Benefits</h2>
          <div class="benefits-content">
            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Improved Flexibility</h3>
              <p>Regular practice gradually loosens tight muscles and increases range of motion in joints. Even if you can't touch your toes at first, you'll notice improvement over time.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Increased Strength</h3>
              <p>Many yoga poses require supporting your body weight in new ways, building functional strength. Strong muscles protect against conditions like arthritis and back pain.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Better Posture</h3>
              <p>As your flexibility and strength improve, your posture follows. Many standing and sitting poses develop core strength, which helps support better posture.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Joint Health</h3>
              <p>Yoga moves joints through their full range of motion, helping prevent degenerative arthritis and relieving disability by "squeezing and soaking" areas of cartilage.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Bone Health</h3>
              <p>Weight-bearing yoga poses strengthen bones and help prevent osteoporosis. Studies have shown yoga can increase bone density in the vertebrae.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Improved Circulation</h3>
              <p>Yoga improves circulation and gets more oxygen to your cells, helping them function better. Twisting poses wring out venous blood from internal organs.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Lower Blood Pressure</h3>
              <p>The relaxation techniques found in yoga can help lower blood pressure, especially beneficial for those with hypertension.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="guide-content-box" id="mental-content">
          <h2>Mental Benefits</h2>
          <div class="benefits-content">
            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Stress Reduction</h3>
              <p>Yoga is known for its ability to reduce stress and promote relaxation. Practice encourages focusing on the present, reducing daily stress and increasing calmness.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Anxiety Relief</h3>
              <p>Research suggests yoga can reduce anxiety. The combination of physical movement, breathwork, and meditation creates a powerful tool for managing anxiety symptoms.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Improved Focus</h3>
              <p>Regular yoga practice improves coordination, reaction time, memory, and even IQ scores. The focused attention needed during practice trains your mind to stay present.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Mood Enhancement</h3>
              <p>Studies have found that yoga can reduce depression and increase serotonin levels. Consistent practice may help alleviate symptoms of depression.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Better Sleep</h3>
              <p>A regular yoga practice helps establish a routine and improves sleep quality. Restorative yoga and yoga nidra are particularly effective for insomnia.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Mindfulness Development</h3>
              <p>Yoga helps develop awareness of your body, feelings, thoughts and the world around you. This mindfulness extends beyond the mat into daily life.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Emotional Resilience</h3>
              <p>Regular practice builds emotional resilience, helping you handle life's challenges with greater ease and adaptability.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="guide-content-box" id="lifestyle-content">
          <h2>Lifestyle Benefits</h2>
          <div class="benefits-content">
            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Healthier Habits</h3>
              <p>Yoga often leads practitioners to adopt healthier lifestyles naturally. Many report developing better eating habits and increased physical activity.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Weight Management</h3>
              <p>Regular practice can support healthy weight management by reducing stress (which can lead to emotional eating) and increasing mindfulness around food choices.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Improved Breathing</h3>
              <p>Yoga teaches proper breathing techniques that can be applied throughout daily life, improving lung function and bringing awareness to this vital process.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Community Connection</h3>
              <p>Participating in group classes provides social benefits and a sense of belonging, which studies show is important for long-term health and happiness.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Personal Growth</h3>
              <p>Yoga often becomes a path for personal development, helping practitioners learn patience, self-compassion, and acceptance both on and off the mat.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Work-Life Balance</h3>
              <p>The mindfulness cultivated in yoga helps many practitioners create healthier boundaries and better work-life balance.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="benefit-card">
              <h3>Complementary Fitness</h3>
              <p>Yoga works well with other forms of exercise, enhancing performance in various activities while reducing injury risk through better flexibility and body awareness.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
